                    h2.project-header CityStats API
                    h3.project-subheader February of 2023 to Present
                    a.project-link(aria-label="link to citystats api" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" role="link" href="https://www.citystats.xyz/states") Visit CityStats API
                    a.project-link.project-repo-link(aria-label="link to citystats repository" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" role="link" href="https://github.com/tomit4/city_stats") Source Code/Documentation
                    h4.project-about About CityStats API
                    p.card.about-card "CityStats API returns essential statistics about all 50 American states as well as the top most populous 229 cities in America."
                    h4.project-about Project Description
                    p.card I wrote CityStats as a way of easily accessing essential statistics about American cities and states. While the US census has its own API, I found it unintuitive and decided to write my own version. Utilizing python's <a class="inline-link" aria-label="link to beautiful soup docs" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" role="link" href="https://beautiful-soup-4.readthedocs.io/">Beautiful Soup Library</a>, I created a web scraping script. This script alongside GNU's cron command line utility, automatically updates the API's data each election cycle (with some human intervention to ensure accuracy). Using a NodeJS/Express server along with a SQLite database, I hosted this API on the Linode Cloud Platform (now Akamai), with the intention that it be used by the general public and developers.
