                .project-card
                    h4.project-about Welcome Traveler!
                    p.card My name is Brian Hayes and you've somehow stumbled across my humble little corner of the web while journeying along! Thanks for taking a look around. I hope you like what you see so far &#128535;.
                    h4.project-about My Story
                    p.card I've worn many hats in my short time on this small beautiful blue ball we call Earth, and I can tell you I've loved every role I've played. I've been a Son, a Student, a Teacher, an Artist, a Clerk, a Concierge, and an Athlete. The most recent hat I've put on has been that of a Programmer! Specifically that of a Full Stack Web Developer &#128512;!
                    p.card Inspired by my best friend/mentor, I took up learning the ins and outs of all things computers a little over 2 years ago. In one of my past lives I was a Digital Artist, so learning to code wasn't completely alien to me as I had more than a basic familiarity with computers working with Adobe Photoshop and Illustrator.
                    p.card During the COVID-19 pandemic, I was working as a Night Auditor at a prestigious hotel. The Hotel Industry wasn't doing too well during that time for obvious reasons, so there was a lot of dead periods during my shifts. Thusly I would find myself, in the dead of night, having all my other tasks completed very early. So...I would break out my laptop (installed with <a class="inline-link" aria-label="link to artix linux website" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" role="link" href="https://artixlinux.org/">an obscure Linux distro</a>), open up my <a class="inline-link" aria-label="link to neovim website" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" role="link" href="https://neovim.io/">NeoVim text editor</a> (like a boss &#128526;), and slowly but surely...I taught myself to code (with lots of feedback from my best friend/mentor of course!).
                    p.card Late in those evenings and early mornings, I would find myself just as engaged as when I was an Art Student... pouring over every detail, endeavoring to find the most natural, but also most efficient line. Computer Programming is probably the most challenging subject I've ever tried to tackle, but... I've worn many hats, engaged in many struggles, and have loved every moment of it all. Computer Programming, and by extension, Web Development, has been, and continues to be, no different.

                    h4.project-about Where I Am Now
                    p.card At the time of this writing, I am running around like a chicken with my head cut off &#128517;! Sometimes I find myself writing a bash script to automate a part of my terminal based workflow. Other times, I'll find myself preoccupied working at <a class="inline-link" aria-label="link to siimee" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" role="link" href="https://siimee.com/">my mentor's Startup company</a>, writing up documentation, adding new features, occassionally creating some... (ahem &#128563;...) <em>quashing</em> some bugs. 
                    p.card I also have signed up at a <a class="inline-link" aria-label="link to code for pdx" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" role="link" href="https://www.codeforpdx.org/">local Code for America branch</a>, where I volunteer my programming skills as a form of community service. My goals currently are to progress in many aspects of life, but specifically in gaining more knowledge about computers and computer programming, and to build a successful career in it!
                    p.card I invite you to take a look at <a class="inline-link" aria-label="blog" role="navigation" href="./blog.html">my blog</a>, where you will find articles that document my learning journey. Feel free to reach out to me via any of the contact/social media options as well! You can find the links to these located both above and below.
                    p.card And be well, Traveler... 
                    p.card Be Well!! ☮️
